## Getting Started (Running Locally)

### Installing Dependencies

#### Java 17

Follow instructions to install the latest version of python for your platform in the [Oracle docs](https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/downloads/).

#### Maven Dependencies

Once you have your Java environment setup and running, install dependencies by navigating to the `/backend` directory and running `mvn dependency:copy-dependencies`. This will install all of the required packages we selected within the `pom.xml` file.

## Running the server

From within the `./backend` directory, run the following command in your terminal:

```
mvn -B package --file pom.xml
```

The server will run on `http://localhost:8080`.


## Testing the application

To test the application, ensure that you're in the `./backend` folder and run the following command
    ```
    mvn -B test
    ```

### Error Handling

#### Response Object

Errors are returned as JSON in the following format:

```
{
    "error": 404,
    "message": "The requested resource was not found."
}
```

#### Response Keys

`error` - Status code of the error that occurred. <br>
`message` - Accompanying error message.

#### Status Codes

`400 (Bad request)` - Your request was not properly formatted. <br>
`404 (Not found)` - The requested resource was not found. <br>
`405 (Method not allowed)` - The request method is not allowed. <br>
`422 (Unprocessable)` - The server understood your request but it could not be processed. <br>
`500 (Internal server error)` - Something went wrong on the server. <br>

### Endpoint Library

#### Pastes

#### `POST /images`

This creates an image and associates it with a generated key that will be used to uniquely identify it.

##### Query Parameters

This endpoint takes in no query parameters

##### Request Body

Accepts a formdata with the keys as:

`file_name`: string - <small> (optional) </small>- Name of the image. <br>
`image`: multipartfile - <small> (required) </small> - Image of the type multpartfile. <br> 


##### Sample Response

`id`: string - Unique key of the image. <br>
`image`: byteArray - Array of bytes representing the image. <br>
`file_name`: string - Name of the image. <br>
`date_created`: date - Date the image was uploaded. <br>

```
{
    "id": "photo-e51e25b5-78ef-4295-975b-56a32da53430",
    "date_created": "2022-09-21T20:48:50.252+00:00",
    "file_name": "test3",
    "image": ""
}
```
